<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Duke's Brand ACC Player of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Elton Brand's trip to the Final Four  
became special before he stepped on the court Friday as the 
sophomore received The Associated Press national player of the year 
award. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-8, 270-pound Brand is the third Duke player to win  
the Adolph Rupp Trophy, following Art Heyman in 1963 and Christian 
Laettner in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
	It is also the third straight year a player from the Atlantic  
Coast Conference received the nation's top individual honor. North 
Carolina's Antawn Jamison won last year and Wake Forest's Tim 
Duncan took home the honor in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the neat things that I have experienced in coaching is  
to be around great young men who have special qualities. Elton is 
certainly that,'' Duke coach Mike Krzyzewski said. ``He is going to 
continue to be a great, great player. He is going to be a lot 
better because there is a lot to this young man.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Entering the Final Four on Saturday night against Michigan  
State, Brand has reached double figures in points and rebounds 17 
times, is shooting 62 percent from the field and has blocked 83 
shots. 
</P>
<P>
	He received 28 votes from AP member newspapers and radio  
stations. Utah senior guard Andre Miller was runner-up with 17. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand missed more than half of his freshman season with a broken  
foot, but recovered to dominate the Goodwill Games. That 
performance earned him many preseason honors heading into the 
1998-99 season. 
</P>
<P>
	He opened the season with a 20-point, 15-rebound effort against  
Fairfield and had a 21-point, 21-rebound game against Fresno State 
in the Great Alaska Shootout. Then Brand's numbers began to 
decline. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand was benched by Krzyzewski on Dec. 12 against Michigan  
because he was out of shape and not living up to his potential. 
After two games of not starting, Brand regrouped and turned his 
season around. 
</P>
<P>
	``It really does seem unreal, it's a like a dream come true,''  
Brand said of receiving the AP honor. ``You work so hard and then 
you have your down points, like coach says, with every journey. But 
I wanted to work hard and have success and that's what I did, 
worked harder.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brand, the only unanimous All-America selection this season, has  
scored in double figures in 36 of 37 games and has 17 double-digit 
rebound games for the nation's best team. 
</P>
<P>
	``He had an amazingly consistent year at the highest level,''  
Krzyzewski said. ``Although he really didn't play the minutes at 
times for the stats that he has, he just lifted our team to a 
different level. 
</P>
<P>
	``Elton is very deserving of this award and I know how proud he  
is. I want to thank him for taking me on his journey.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
