<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chargers Sign Rams Linebacker Hill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- The San Diego Chargers agreed Friday to a  
two-year contract with St. Louis Rams linebacker Eric Hill. Terms 
were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot 2-inch, 258-pound Hill started 15 games last season  
and had 86 tackles, one sack, one interception, three passes 
defended and one forced fumble. 
</P>
<P>
	A first-round draft pick of the Phoenix Cardinals in 1989, Hill  
played nine seasons with the Arizona Cardinals before joining the 
Rams as a free agent in 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill, 32, heads into his 11th season with 143 starts in 148  
games, 1,169 tackles, nine sacks, one interception, 13 passes 
defended, four forced fumbles and six fumble recoveries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
