<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-26 16:44:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Super Lightweight Fight Set for May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Miguel Angel Gonzalez and Konstantin Tszyu  
are finally set again to fight for the WBC super lightweight crown 
-- although where is not yet certain. 
</P>
<P>
	The World Boxing Council said Friday that the fight originally  
scheduled for Nov. 28 now has been set for May 15. A location is 
due to be announced ``in a short period.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The winner is supposed to face former champion Julio Cesar  
Chavez. 
</P>
<P>
	The fight between Gonzalez of Mexico and the Russian-born Tszyu  
was first delayed by an injury to Gonzalez, then by Gonzalez's 
court suit to drop promoter Don King. 
</P>
<P>
	That was settled March 4 when King agreed to share promotion of  
Gonzalez's next four fights with Dan Goossen. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez's only loss against 42 victories came against Oscar De  
La Hoya. He also had a controversial draw against Chavez a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Tszyu is 21-1-1. He earlier held the IBF junior middleweight  
crown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
