<HEADLINE> N.C. Executes Man Who Killed Inmate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- A man who killed a fellow prison inmate,  
then fired his lawyers and asked to be executed was put to death by 
injection Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	James David Rich, 26, pleaded guilty to stabbing Paul Gwyn at  
the Eastern Correctional Institution in 1994. Rich was serving a 
life sentence for another murder at the time. 
</P>
<P>
	He said he killed Gwyn because he didn't like an educational  
program at the prison and wanted to be transferred to another one. 
</P>
<P>
	In his last statement, Rich praised God and asked for mercy for  
the world. 
</P>
<P>
	Rich represented himself at his trial, later fired appeals  
lawyers and asked to be executed. However, some of his supporters 
said he was mentally ill and that he sometimes asked that his 
execution not go forward. 
</P>
