<HEADLINE> Two Dead in Texas Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- A two-seat helicopter being used to take aerial  
photographs of commercial real estate crashed in a parking lot in a 
dense business district Friday, killing the pilot and the 
photographer. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the crash was under investigation. Witnesses said  
the helicopter began spinning out of control before it dropped out 
of the sky. 
</P>
<P>
	``The rotor stopped spinning and then the body of the helicopter  
started spinning ... and it just literally dropped straight down, 
like a top falling out of the sky,'' witness Ben Samuels said. 
</P>
<P>
	No one on the ground was injured.  
</P>
