<HEADLINE> IRS Tax Filing Statistics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Selected figures from this year's tax filing season through 	
March 19 in comparison with the same period last year: 
</P>
<P>
                           *Returns Filed 	
</P>
<P>
	--57.2 million, up 2.1 percent. 	
</P>
<P>
                         *Electronic filing 	
</P>
<P>
	--Total, 22.8 million, up 15.8 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Computer, 18.3 million, up 22.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Telephone, 4.5 million, down 5.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
 *Refunds 
</P>
<P>
	--43.6 million, up 1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Total: $70.2 billion, up 16.3 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Average: $1,609, up 15.2 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	--Direct deposit: $17.8 million, up 22.4 percent.  
</P>
