<HEADLINE> Sore Hip Forces Daly Withdrawal  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PONTE VEDRA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- John Daly withdrew from The  
Players Championship today because of a sore hip, an exit far less 
dramatic than his one two years ago following an all-night drinking 
session. 
</P>
<P>
	Daly's hip has been ailing all year, and he walked with a  
significant limp toward the end of his opening-round 83 on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	He came to the course to tell tournament officials he could not  
continue and left without comment. 
</P>
<P>
