<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ford Recalls 945,000 Cars, Trucks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) -- Ford Motor Co. is recalling about 945,000  
cars and trucks to replace potentially defective cruise-control 
cables that could cause the accelerator to stick. 
</P>
<P>
	The voluntary recall announced Friday affects some 1998 and 1999  
models equipped with optional cruise control. The models are the 
Ford Explorer and Mercury Mountaineer sport utility vehicles, Ford 
Ranger pickup, Mustang sport coupe, and 1999 Super Duty F-series 
pickup and chassis-cab. 
</P>
<P>
	Chassis-cabs are commonly used for motor homes and commercial  
vehicles. Of the 945,000 vehicles affected, 35,673 are in Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	Ford is in the process of obtaining cruise-control cables to  
replace the defective ones and does not expect to have them in 
stock before mid-May. Until then, Ford is warning owners not to use 
their cruise-control system; dealers on request will disable the 
system at no charge. 
</P>
<P>
	Ford said in a statement that in some of the vehicles the  
cruise-control cable could interfere with a pulley and prevent the 
accelerator from returning to idle when the cruise control is 
disengaged. The result is the car could continue to move at the set 
speed and cause an accident. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no reports of that happening, and operation of  
the vehicle is unaffected when the cruise control is off, Ford 
said. The problem was discovered by Ford engineers during a regular 
engineering review, spokeswoman Karen Shaughnessy said. 
</P>
<P>
	The largest number of recalled vehicles is the Explorer and  
Mountaineer twins -- about 567,000. Ford did not reveal how much it 
expects the recall to cost. 
</P>
<P>
	Owners of the affected vehicles will be notified by mail  
starting Monday. Customers also can call Ford's customer relations 
number, 800-392-3673, to find out if their vehicle is subject to 
the recall; callers will be asked for the vehicle identification 
number, which can typically be found on the registration, insurance 
certificate or the door pillar. 
</P>
<P>
	The same information also can be obtained at a new Ford Web  
site: www.recall.ford.com. 



</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
