<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	Cort Business Services rose 6 to 22 3/4.  
</P>
<P>
	The Fairfax, Va.-based furniture-rental company agreed to be  
acquired by a group including Cort managers and the investment firm 
Bruckmann Rosser Sherill &AMP; Co. for $363 million in stock plus 
assumed debt of $90 million. 

</P>
<P>
	Guess? rose 3/8 to 7 3/16.  
</P>
<P>
	The Los Angeles-based apparel manufacturer relaunches its Web  
site Monday. The site features an online catalog, and later this 
year, retailers will be able to order merchandise for their stores 
online. 

</P>
<P>
	Inacom fell 4 to 7 3/16.  
</P>
<P>
	The Omaha, Neb.-based information technology company expects  
first-quarter earnings to fall below Wall Street analysts' 
estimates. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	SpeedUS.com rose 1 11/16 to 3 5/32.  
</P>
<P>
	The New York-based company has installed a new technology  
allowing it to broadcast videos online. SpeedUS.com is a high-speed 
Internet service. 

</P>
<P>
	CyberShop International rose 2 1/4 13 1/8.  
</P>
<P>
	The Jersey City, N.J.-based online merchant unveiled its  
CyberShop Auctions Web site, which will auction off discounted 
apparel. 

</P>
<P>
	OneMain.com fell 7 9/16 to 32.  
</P>
<P>
	The Southhampton, N.Y.-based Internet service provider fell one  
day after its initial public offering. The offering was priced at 
$22. The stock opened at $36 on Thursday and closed at $39.56 1/4. 

</P>
<P>
	Deltek Systems rose 1 13/16 to 11.  
</P>
<P>
	The McLean, Va.-based company plans to buy back up to 1 million  
common shares. The business software company said it will use the 
shares for general purposes including stock option and purchase 
plans. 

</P>
<P>
	Chronimed fell 1 9/16 to 5 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
	The Minneapolis-based health care company expects its earnings  
for the second half of its fiscal year 1999 will be ``significantly 
below'' analyst expectations. 

</P>
<P>
	Applied Analytical fell 4 5/8 to 12 5/8.  
</P>
<P>
	The investment firm Morgan Keegan downgraded Applied  
Analytical's stock. 

</P>
</TEXT>
