<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hurricanes Broadcaster Hirsch Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Sonny Hirsch, a broadcaster for the University of  
Miami for nearly 30 years, has died at 65. 
</P>
<P>
	Hirsch's body was found in his Miami Lakes apartment. Friends  
said he apparently had a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
	Hirsch did play-by-play of Miami football, basketball and  
baseball games from 1958 to 1971 and again from 1983 to 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	``He always showed a tremendous amount of care about the  
University of Miami and his job, and was one of the best at what he 
did,'' said Miami Dolphins coach Jimmy Johnson, the Hurricanes' 
coach from 1984 to 1988. 
</P>
<P>
	Hirsch also hosted sportscasts and sports talk shows, primarily  
on WIOD-AM. He was inducted into the University of Miami Hall of 
Fame a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	He was an official scorer at Florida Marlins games since their  
first season in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
