<HEADLINE> NBA Suspends Suns' Chapman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The NBA suspended Phoenix guard Rex Chapman for  
one game without pay and fined him $5,000 for making contact with a 
referee while complaining about a call in the Suns' loss to the 
Trail Blazers in Portland Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Chapman grazed referee Scott Foster in the head while flailing  
his arms in protest when he was called for a foul after being run 
over by Portland's Rasheed Wallace with 3:34 remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Chapman was thrown out of the game for the incident. The penalty  
forced him to sit out Friday night's home game against the New York 
Knicks. 
