<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pacific Internet Revenues Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SINGAPORE (AP) -- Pacific Internet Ltd., a Singapore Internet  
service provider listed on the U.S. Nasdaq composite stock index, 
announced Friday that its revenues rose 47 percent last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Driven by a 66 percent increase in subscribers, Pacific Internet  
said 1998 revenues rose to 71.9 million Singapore dollars (U.S. 
$41.5 million), up from 48.9 million Singapore dollars (U.S. $28.26 
million) in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said it had 203,490 subscribers in Singapore, Hong  
Kong and the Philippines as of the end of 1998 and planned to seek 
the acquisition of new Internet companies in the Asia Pacific 
region this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said its net income also improved last year, to 12.2  
million Singapore dollars (U.S. $7 million) after a loss of 9.8 
million Singapore dollars (U.S. $5.66 million) in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
