<HEADLINE> Bryant Reeves Undergoes Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- Vancouver center Bryant  
Reeves underwent successful arthroscopic surgery Friday to repair a 
slight cartilege tear in his right knee and will be out for up to 
four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	In placing Reeves on the injured list, the Grizzlies activated  
rookie forward Makhtar Ndiaye, who began the season on the injured 
list with a strained shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Reeves' injury caps a frustrating campaign for the four-year  
veteran, whose six-year $66 million salary kicked in at the start 
of this season. After reporting to training camp almost 40 pounds 
overweight, Reeves was relegated to the bench for the first nine 
games. 
</P>
<P>
	Averaging 10.8 points and 13 rebounds over 25 games, Reeves  
suffered the injury before Monday's game at Phoenix. 
</P>
