<HEADLINE> Timberwolves Bring Back Robinson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- James Robinson is back in Minnesota.  
</P>
<P>
	Badly in need of outside shooting help, the Timberwolves signed  
the guard to a 10-day contract Friday. Robinson, whose nickname is 
``Hollywood,'' played for the Wolves during the 1996-97 season. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson, who came to Minnesota the first time as part of a  
trade for Isaiah Rider, was cut by the Los Angeles Clippers last 
week. He holds Wolves records for points in a quarter (23) and 
3-pointers made in a quarter (six) and a half (six). He set all 
three marks at Cleveland on Dec. 30, 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wolves made room for Robinson on the roster by waiving  
forward Brian Evans, who was acquired from New Jersey in this 
month's Stephon Marbury trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
