<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NCAA Final Four Notebook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Duke's Shane Battier has a  
reputation for defense and taking charges. So, when the sophomore 
opened up on offense with a 27-point game against Maryland, the 
Blue Devils were suitably impressed. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Mike Krzyzewski recalled someone asking Duke's Chris  
Carrawell about all those points by Battier. 
</P>
<P>
	``He said, `Well, he wasn't the Naismith High School Player of  
the Year because he took charges. He must have shot the ball 
somewhere along the line.''' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *``MY FAVORITE COACH!'':* On their first night at the Final  
Four, coaches Jim Calhoun of Connecticut, Jim O'Brien of Ohio 
State, Tom Izzo of Michigan State and Mike Krzyzewski of Duke spent 
some time together. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Brien, who will try to end a personal 18-game losing streak  
against Calhoun in Saturday's semifinals, recalled the UConn 
coach's arrival in the room. 
</P>
<P>
	``When he sees all of us,'' O'Brien said, ``he says `Tom, it's  
nice to see you. Mike, it's nice to see you. Jim, it's REALLY nice 
to see you.''' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *GET THE POINT:* Point guard Mateen Cleaves of Michigan State  
tried to define the requirements of his position. 
</P>
<P>
	``You've got to be able to take constructive criticism,'' he  
said. ``You've got to not be afraid. You've got to have a good 
personality. You've got to know everybody's personality on the 
team, who, how, when and where to get them the ball. You've got to 
run the team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sounds like a coach.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *ARCHITECT IN TRAINING:* Tropicana Field, site of the Final  
Four, has some bad memories for Duke coach Mike Krzyzewski, whose 
team blew a 17-point lead to Kentucky in the regional finals in 
this building a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Besides losing the game, there were the leaks in the building,  
leaving puddles here and there. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach K is featured in a current Nike commercial working on a  
sand sculpture of the field and was asked about the real building 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's pretty nice, isn't it,'' Krzyzewski said. ``It's a lot  
less wet than it was last year. Fixed up all the leaks. I think 
that's why they had me do that. Last year when we were here, it was 
pretty wet. They fixed this place up nice. I'm glad they used my 
models to do the repairs. It was nice of them to do that.'' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *COACHES VS. CANCER:* In 1993, Missouri coach Norm Stewart won a  
personal battle with cancer and launched a partnership between the 
American Cancer Society and the National Association of Basketball 
Coaches, raising funds to fight the disease. 
</P>
<P>
	Now, 28 coaches including John Wooden, Dean Smith, John Thompson  
and Bob Knight, Mike Krzyzewski and Jim Calhoun have signed 400 
lithographs and 200 basketballs that will be sold at the Final Four 
and elsewhere with proceeds to benefit Coaches Against Cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	``The coaches realize that together they are capable of helping  
the Amercian Cancer Society maximize its fund-raising potential, 
while generating much-needed awareness,'' said Tom Ford, assistant 
executive director of the National Association of Basketball 
Coaches. ``The unique teamwork exhibited by these coaching legends 
is an inspiration.'' 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *ALSO-RANS:* With three No. 1 seeds in the Final Four, Ohio  
State sometimes feels like an outsider, coming in as a No. 4. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel like we're playing an undercard,'' guard Scoonie Penn  
said. ``We probably don't get spoken about as much as the other 
teams. ... But I feel that's OK with us. I feel like we've been in 
that situation all season, kind of played the underdog role. It fit 
us well so we'll continue playing it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	If it's any consolation, the last time three top seeds made it  
to the finals, Arizona was a No. 4 and won the national 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *POLL WATCHERS: With No. 1 Duke, No. 2 Connecticut and No. 3  
Michigan State in the Final Four, it marked the first time since 
1974 the top three teams in the final Associated Press poll made it 
to the season's last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1974, No. 1 North Carolina State, No. 2 UCLA and No. 3  
Marquette made it and NC State won the title. 



</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
