<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ewing Hits 10,000-Rebound Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Patrick Ewing grabbed his 10,000th NBA rebound  
Friday night, becoming the 12th player in the league's history to 
score at least 20,000 points and grab 10,000 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The Knicks center entered the game against Phoenix needing four  
rebounds to reach the milestone. He got it with 3:49 remaining in 
the first quarter on a miss by Suns center Luc Longley. 
</P>
<P>
	The game was stopped briefly while the achievement was announced  
to polite applause from the America West Arena crowd. 
</P>
<P>
	Ewing, in his 14th NBA season, entered the game with 22,461  
points, 17th on the career list. 
</P>
<P>
	The others on the 20,000-point, 10,000-rebound list are Kareem  
Abdul-Jabbar, Wilt Chamberlain, Karl Malone, Moses Malone, Elvin 
Hayes, Hakeem Olajuwon, Robert Parish, Elgin Baylor, Charles 
Barkley, Walt Bellamy and Bob Pettit. 
</P>
