wound up 20th at 187.311. 
</P>
<P>
	The 25 fastest qualifiers locked up starting spots in the 43-car  
field, with the rest of the lineup to be set Saturday following the 
final round of time trials. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the drivers who failed to make the top 25 and will have to  
either try again Saturday or stand on their first-day laps were 
former series champions Dale Earnhardt, who was 38th, and Darrell 
Waltrip, 46th of the 48 drivers who made qualifying attempts. 
</P>
