	On a track where crashes were commonplace during the first two  
Winston Cup weekends, the only incident among NASCAR's elite came 
during qualifying when Ken Bouchard smacked the wall hard. 
</P>
<P>
	Bouchard, who suffered a concussion, was flown by helicopter to  
a Dallas hospital, where he underwent tests and evaluation. Track 
officials said the driver from Fitchburg, Mass., was awake and 
alert, but was expected to be kept overnight for observation. 


</P>
